# Known-good DEPLOYED binary baseline for `west darling-doctor` check 3.
#
# These are the md5s of the last-known-good deployed closure binaries in the install prefix. The
# doctor compares the deployed dyld (both copies) / mldr / darlingserver against these by default.
#
# Format: one "key = md5" per line; '#' comments. Keys: dyld, mldr, dserver.
# UPDATE this file (and note why + which Bead) whenever a legitimate rebuild changes what is
# deployed — otherwise the doctor will (correctly) flag the new deploy as a baseline mismatch.
#
# Current baseline (2026-07-03, task #116 A0-ARCH stage 1): darlingserver updated to the
# A0-ARCH stage 0+1 landing (fuzzer DSERVER_SCHED_FUZZ; typed wake tokens; savedResumeContext
# jumpToResume fix; interrupt-desync survival guards; built with -g for live triage; branch
# fix/a0-arch-redesign, see tests/A0-ARCH-STAGE1.md). Acceptance: synth gate 13/13 gating
# green; brew xz 2/2 strict green; the single full-gate wget freeze proved PRE-EXISTING
# (baseline 886d13af froze the same way in an 11-run A/B, ~1/10 rate; fingerprint ~57.4k
# pthread_canceled storm then all-parked; tracked for stages 2/3); perf A/B within noise
# (nestwait −1.2%, 300xtrue identical); fuzz survival better than baseline (4/6 vs 5/6 RED).
# dyld/mldr unchanged (ring + DCC kept).
#   dyld    79b22273  (dyld-733.6, boot-compatible with the deployed 06-15 closure)
#   mldr    f0cd2a82  (perf#21b compact-fd band)
#   dserver a889e85f  (ring + A0 fixes a3de8c2 + A0-ARCH stages 0/1/1b/1c)
# Previous dserver baseline: 886d13af (a3de8c2, task #113) — backup in job tmp.

dyld    = 79b22273481ea61ab63c0606c23ab300
mldr    = f0cd2a82efc4cb4614b63cabac0168f8
